#### Key Concepts

1. Students apply the problem solving process to new situations.  They should be able to explain the steps of the problem solving process they went through and why they made certain choices. 

1. Students problem solving strategies should will expand to include visual methods (<i>draw a diagram or picture, make a systematic list, charts, graphs, tables</i>)

#### Common Difficulties

Again make sure to accomodate for the differences in time that these problems will take and have extension activities where necessary.

